      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUR SHERALEE (5) placed three back at this track then out of the placings last couple but moves to box 5 this time where she has performed well. Has good speed and will be prominent despite the squeeze draw. Can make amends this time. SEBON STAR (1) had the drop on the lead from the squeeze box before taking over turning, drawing clear to score (20.71) at this track in a TG1-4W over 342m. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Deserves serious consideration again. CHRISTOFF (4) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing seventh (31.61) last time in a Grade 6 at Mt Gambier. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Leading chance. LIONESS EYES (2) cannot be left out after leading and holding on for a placing last start.",
